"title": "5903: maturity, physical",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5903: maturity, physical",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In the OT, reaching adulthood brought with it certain privileges and responsibilities.</p>\n<h2>Growth to physical and psychological maturity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ's normal childhood is evidence of his full humanity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:26\">1SA 2:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:80\">LUK 1:80</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:40\">LUK 2:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:11\">1CO 13:11</a></p>\n<h2>The responsibilities of maturity in the Israelite community</h2>\n<h3>The payment of atonement money</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:11-Exod30:16\">EXO 30:11–30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:25-Exod38:26\">EXO 38:25–38:26</a></p>\n<h3>Eligibility for military service</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:2-Num1:3\">NUM 1:2–1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:45\">NUM 1:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:2\">NUM 26:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:5\">2CH 25:5</a></p>\n<h3>Accountability for actions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:29\">NUM 14:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:11\">NUM 32:11</a></p>\n<h3>Inheritance of the land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:52-Num26:54\">NUM 26:52–26:54</a></p>\n<h3>Serving Levites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:24-Num8:25\">NUM 8:24–8:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:24\">1CH 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:27\">1CH 23:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:8\">EZR 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Maturity should produce wisdom</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:12\">JOB 12:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:10\">JOB 15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:6-Job32:9\">JOB 32:6–32:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:7\">PRO 7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:13\">ECC 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Respect should be shown to the mature</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:32\">LEV 19:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:4\">JOB 32:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:22\">PRO 23:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1-1Tim5:2\">1TI 5:1–5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Maturity of years seen as God's blessing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:1\">GEN 24:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:15\">RUT 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:28</a></p>\n<h2>The maturity of crops for harvest used as a metaphor</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:13\">JOL 3:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:35-John4:36\">JHN 4:35–4:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:1-Amos8:2\">AMO 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:37-Matt9:38\">MAT 9:37–9:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:1-Luke10:2\">LUK 10:1–10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:26-Mark4:29\">MRK 4:26–4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:15\">REV 14:15</a></p>",
